31. She passes to her mother's family, the Libones. It was a plebeian family: we hear of a L. Scribonius Libo, tribune of the plebs Β. c. 16. Scribonia was sister to L. Scribonius Libo, who followed the fortunes of Pompey throughout the civil war, and commanded the Pompeian fleet off Brundusium before Pharsalia. His daughter was married to Sextus Pompey: and in B.c. 40 he was an important enough personage for Augustus to think it worth while to con- ciliate him by manylng his sister Scribonia, though much older than himself.
